Yana Troyanova* was unable to challenge her status as a foreign agent, claiming that she did not receive funding from foreign sources. The court sided with the Ministry of Justice.

According to SHOT, the Ministry of Justice believes that Troyanova is under foreign influence:

- she made a number of publications condemning the Russian Federation, which were actively supported by foreign media;

— participated in the “March of Mothers”, in a single picket in support of Navalny;

— the fact of her support for other foreign agents was revealed;

— She actively gave interviews to Dud*, Lazareva*, Dozhd*.

